* test-qm.mqsc — MQSC applied at QM startup to configure authentication
* matching the local QM1 setup (CHCKCLNT REQDADM, DEV.APP.SVRCONN with MCAUSER app).
*
* The IBM MQ developer image already creates DEV.APP.SVRCONN and DEV.AUTHINFO,
* this file just ensures the settings we test against are explicitly set.

* Ensure channel auth records are disabled (matches local QM1: CHLAUTH DISABLED)
ALTER QMGR CHLAUTH(DISABLED)

* Configure connection authentication:
*   CHCKCLNT(REQDADM) — password required for mqm-group (admin) users,
*                        optional for application users.
*   ADOPTCTX(YES)     — adopt the MQ context of the authenticated user.
ALTER AUTHINFO(DEV.AUTHINFO) AUTHTYPE(IDPWOS) CHCKCLNT(REQDADM) CHCKLOCL(OPTIONAL) ADOPTCTX(YES)

* Activate the authentication configuration
REFRESH SECURITY TYPE(CONNAUTH)
